"n.量子；定量 【英】 n.定量; 量子(any of the small subdivisions of a quantized physical magnitude) 【记】 quant(数量)＋um→定 量 【同】 同根词：quantity(数 量，总量); quantitative(数量的) n. 定量; 量子 【例】the quantum of rainfall(降雨总量) 【记】quant数量, um一定量 【参】quantity(n 数量, 总量) 【记】quantity + sum 总和 quantum (n.)  1610s, ""one's share or portion,"" from Latin quantum (plural quanta) ""as much as, so much as; how much? how far? how great an extent?"" neuter singular of correlative pronomial adjective quantus ""as much"" (see quantity). Introduced in physics directly from Latin by Max Planck, 1900; reinforced by Einstein, 1905. Quantum theory is from 1912; quantum mechanics, 1922; quantum jump is first recorded 1954; quantum leap, 1963, often figurative."
